Insecurity and Fraud
The current esports market is completely insecure. Even the top-tier teams are facing fraud and non-payments of prize money. The same goes for sponsors and advertisers that face non-delivery. This is even more so for amateur teams and small and medium-sized sponsors and advertisers.
Market Fragmentation
All of the esports market participants have no single go-to marketplace to make advertising or sponsorship deals, transfer players or search for tournaments. And everything has to be done manually; an all-in-one database is absent. And this leads to lots of time and effort spent on development. This, in turn, causes a significant decrease in market growth.
Limited Universe and Possibilities
Very limited market universe to enter, as the stakes are too high for 1 OOk+ small and medium-sized advertisers and sponsors that are willing to promote their brands and products. Millions of gamers and teams don't have a clear cut-point due to absence of business tools for team management, recruitment, analytics, sales, marketing, etc.

DreamTeam acts as a secure transactional point for esports, just like PayPal. It encompasses prize-money payouts, playersâ salaries and transfers, sponsorship and advertising deals or media rights sales - all enabled by the security of payment via smart contracts.
All-In-One Network

Token
functionality

DreamTeam Token is the only intra-platform DreamTeam currency. Every transaction on the platform will require the use of DreamTeam Tokens. Token application is fully supported by the blockchain technology and can be used for:
Payment of all smart contracts obligations:
Players Compensations
Players Transfers
Sponsorship and Media Rights Sales
Advertising Agreements
Tournaments Prize Payout
Paid platform features:
Premium Accounts
Researches
Verified Rank
One-time Services
Other features:
Buying Games, Software, Hardware and More.
Example of a smart contract:
A team participates in a tournament and after securing a winning place, the prize money is automatically transferred to their account, according to the preset smart contract rules. Consecutively, all players receive their share of the prize money.
*DreamTeam charges a fee for each smart contract execution.
Example of a platform feature:
A player purchases a premium account and is able to apply for any vacancy, even to a full team, without limit. Playerâs applications will feature at the top of the list and upon being selected to a team finalist list, and he/she will receive a corresponding notification.

The number of DreamTeam Tokens is strictly limited to the Phase #1 and Phase #2 Token Sale.

After that no more DreamTeam Tokens will enter into circulation.

How to Withdraw DreamTeam Tokens

The DreamTeam Token Sale Audit was completed on May 19, 2018.

If youâre a DreamTeam contributor , please follow this guide to receive your DreamTeam Tokens.

  • Add and verify your ETH wallet in your personal account in the tokens destination field at the Profile tab of your account on token.dreamteam.gg. To successfully receive DreamTeam Tokens, please, specify the wallet that supports ERC20 interface.
    We recommend to use: Myetherwallet, Mist, MetaMask.
  • Confirm your wallet address via the link sent to your email;
  • Wait for the transfer of your DreamTeam Tokens into your wallet that will happen within 30 days after the completion of the above steps.

Important notice:

If youâve already registered your personal wallet on token.dreamteam.gg, we highly recommend you change your password and enable two-factor authentication for security reasons. These safety measures should be taken before specifying your personal ERC20 compatible wallet where you want to receive your DreamTeam Tokens.
